OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1771916638
OL,3,CBBC apologises after racial slur is
OL,4,Cbroadcast during Bafta ceremony
OL,6,FA BBC spokesperson said: "Some viewers
OL,7,Fmay have heard strong and offensive
OL,8,Flanguage during the Bafta Film Awards
OL,9,F2026.
OL,11,F"This arose from involuntary verbal
OL,12,Ftics associated with Tourette
OL,13,Fsyndrome, and was not intentional. We
OL,14,Fapologise for any offence caused by
OL,15,Fthe language heard."
OL,17,FThe BBC did not comment on its
OL,18,Fdecision not to cut the language from
OL,19,Fthe final programme, which aired
OL,20,Faround two hours after it was filmed.
OL,26,@nD@ZOUsD@AOUwD@TO]
