CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1771916638
OL,3,CBBC apologises after racial slur is
OL,4,Cbroadcast during Bafta ceremony
OL,6,F"Tourette syndrome is a disability and
OL,7,Fthe tics you have heard tonight are
OL,8,Finvoluntary, which means the person
OL,9,Fwho has Tourette syndrome has no
OL,10,Fcontrol over their language. We
OL,11,Fapologise if you were offended."
OL,13,FI Swear tells the story of Scottish
OL,14,FTourette syndrome campaigner John
OL,15,FDavidson, who developed the condition
OL,16,Fwhen he was 12.
OL,18,FMr Davidson was made an MBE in 2019
OL,19,Ffor his efforts to increase
OL,20,Funderstanding of Tourette Syndrome and
OL,21,Fhelp families deal with the condition.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
