PN,30607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1771916638
OL,3,CBBC apologises after racial slur is
OL,4,Cbroadcast during Bafta ceremony
OL,6,F"Once in a while these things happen -
OL,7,FI don't think black people in the
OL,8,Fcountry are going to be traumatised...
OL,9,FBBC made a mistake, a horrible
OL,10,Fmistake. I think that the two actors
OL,11,Fstanding there are the people who
OL,12,Fwould've been most embarrassed because
OL,13,Fthey wouldn't have known what was
OL,14,Fgoing on, and Delroy Lindo and Michael
OL,15,FB Jordan are the ones who need the
OL,16,Fbiggest apology, this is a huge, huge
OL,17,Fmistake."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1771916638
OL,3,CBBC apologises after racial slur is
OL,4,Cbroadcast during Bafta ceremony
OL,6,F"This is something that we should view
OL,7,Fas a mistake rather than a
OL,8,Frepresentation of our country," she
OL,9,Fadded.
OL,11,FEd Palmer, vice chairman of Tourettes
OL,12,FAction said the BBC should have
OL,13,Fconsidered bleeping out the slur.
OL,15,F"This is really one of the most acute
OL,16,Fexamples of where something that is a
OL,17,Fdisability can cause quite
OL,18,Funderstandably huge amounts of offence
OL,19,Fto someone," he said on Times Radio.
OL,26,@wD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
